Title: randomPrintableASCII
Description:
Generates a string with a random set of ASCII characters. All characters are printable.
If you pass length < 0, the behavior of the function is undefined.
length — String length in bytes. Positive integer.
String with a random set of ASCII printable characters. String
Examples: SELECT number, randomPrintableASCII(30) as str, length(str) FROM system.numbers LIMIT 3
